    <fr:title text="Subset">Subset</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>A set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Gamma ]]></fr:tex> is a <html:strong>subset</html:strong> of a set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Delta ]]></fr:tex> iff: every member of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Gamma ]]></fr:tex> is also a member of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Delta ]]></fr:tex>.
There's a symbol for this: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Gamma  \subseteq  \Delta ]]></fr:tex> means that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Gamma ]]></fr:tex> is a subset of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Delta ]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
